<TITLE> 3 Ijtema pilgrims killed in road accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com)  Three devotees were killed early on Sunday on their way to attend the Akheri Munajat, or final prayer, of the three-day Biswa Ijtema beside the Turag river on Dhaka's outskirts. The identities of the victims could not be immediately verified, police said. Savar police sub-inspector Abu Taher said a middle-aged devotee was crushed under the wheel of a truck as he was crossing the Dhaka-Aricha highway near Fulbari bus stand at around 7am. He said two others were killed on the same highway  one in front Padma Printers at around 7:30am and the other near Aminbazar bus stand at around 8am  as fast-moving vehicles knocked the down. Hundreds of thousands of devotees from home and abroad joined in the Akheri Munajat Sunday noon to mark the end of the world's second largest Muslim congregation after the Hajj. WOMAN DIES IN SAVAR ACCIDENT In another road accident, a woman was killed when a bus hit her on the Dhaka-Tangail highway at Tongibari in Savar at around 9am. Ashulia police station sub-inspector Murad Ali said the deceased had been identified as Monwara Begum, 45, wife of Nurul Islam from Madhabpur upazila in Habiganj district. Police said separate cases were filed in connection with all four accidents. bdn
